cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) seems likely as the paper deals with properties of sets of natural numbers and their numbering, which can be seen as a logical topic. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a possibility as the paper discusses the structure of left-r.e. sets under inclusion modulo a finite set, which can be related to information theory. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) could be a relevant sub-category as the paper deals with the complexity of determining whether a property can be made into itself. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possibility as the paper deals with the structure of sets of natural numbers and their properties. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the property of being Martin-Löf random, which is related to randomness and security.
